<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,680]" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,583,608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet is in honor of David C. Lightfoot, desert biologist, specialist in North American Orthoptera, and one of the organizers of the 
<collectionCode box="[780,864,620,644]" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">UNMC</collectionCode>
2011 expedition; with our thanks for bringing the 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,655,680]" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen to our attention.
</paragraph>
